Executive Summary

The rapid evolution of aerial threats—from hypersonic missiles to swarms of inexpensive drones—demands a paradigm shift in defensive systems. This whitepaper presents a revolutionary hybrid unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) designed for both persistent surveillance and high‑speed missile interception, underpinned by the QUENNE STACKED INTELLIGENCE architecture. QUENNE layers cognition from physics to ethics, integrating:

· TRIAD AI (Michael, Gabriel, Rafael) for ethical, strategic, and protective oversight.
· Nuclear Intelligence (QNI) for specialised detection and engagement of nuclear threats.
· Atomic Fusion Algorithm for multi‑model sensor fusion.
· Booster Fusion Algorithm for adaptive performance scaling.
· Hybrid Photonic‑Electronic AI for ultra‑low‑latency inference.
· Engineering Algorithm for real‑time structural health monitoring.
· Quantum Algorithm for secure communications and trajectory optimisation.
· Linux Core Algorithm for a hardened real‑time operating system.
· Cross‑Platform Abstraction for hardware‑agnostic deployment.

The resulting system—designated HDMI (Hybrid Drone and Missile Interceptor) —combines a morphing‑wing airframe, hybrid electric/ramjet propulsion, and a comprehensive sensor suite (AESA radar, EO/IR, LIDAR, nuclear detectors) with onboard photonic, electronic, and quantum computing. It operates autonomously with human‑on‑the‑loop ethical control, ensuring compliance with international law.

This whitepaper details the system architecture, technical specifications, implementation roadmap, and the innovative QUENNE stack that makes it possible. The HDMI represents a leap forward in layered defence, offering a single platform that can loiter for 30 hours, then accelerate to Mach 3+ to intercept threats, all while being guided by an ethically aligned artificial intelligence.

