2.1 Human Authority: TRIAD AI

· Michael (Ethical Intelligence): A hybrid symbolic‑neural engine that evaluates every proposed action against Rules of Engagement (ROE) and international law. It outputs a permissibility score and a human‑readable explanation.
· Gabriel (Strategic Intelligence): A reinforcement‑learning‑based mission planner that integrates with command networks, updates plans based on evolving threats, and coordinates with allied assets.
· Rafael (Protective Intelligence): Monitors system health, detects cyber‑attacks, and initiates evasive manoeuvres or safe return‑to‑base if critical failures occur.

2.2 Nuclear Intelligence (QNI)

Dedicated to nuclear threat detection, QNI fuses data from gamma‑ray spectrometers, neutron detectors, and radar track files. It applies spectral fingerprinting and trajectory analysis to confirm nuclear warheads, and enforces a two‑person (human) rule before authorising engagement.

2.3 Atomic Fusion Algorithm

A multi‑model cognitive fusion engine that combines data from heterogeneous sensors (radar, EO/IR, LIDAR, acoustic, external tracks) into a probabilistic world model updated at 100 Hz. It uses attention‑based neural networks and Kalman filters to track hundreds of objects simultaneously.

2.4 Booster Fusion Algorithm

Manages the transition between loiter (electric) and sprint (ramjet) modes. Using model predictive control (MPC), it commands wing morphing, thrust vectoring, and throttle to achieve smooth, rapid transitions while optimising fuel consumption.

2.5 Hybrid Photonic‑Electronic AI

· Photonic Core: Performs ultra‑fast, low‑power matrix operations for image processing, radar pulse compression, and signal filtering.
· Electronic Core: Handles complex decision‑making, control loops, and communication protocols. The two domains share memory via a high‑speed optical interconnect.

2.6 Engineering Algorithm

A digital twin of the airframe runs in real time, fed by fibre‑optic strain, temperature, and vibration sensors. It predicts fatigue life, detects damage, and advises flight envelope limits to prevent structural failure.

2.7 Quantum Algorithm

· Secure Communication: Implements free‑space Quantum Key Distribution (QKD) for ground links, ensuring that commands cannot be intercepted.
· Optimisation: Solves mixed‑integer programming problems (e.g., optimal intercept trajectories) using quantum annealing, with a classical fallback.

2.8 Linux Core Algorithm

A hardened, real‑time Linux kernel (PREEMPT_RT) provides deterministic scheduling, containerisation (Docker/LXC), and security features (SELinux, IMA). It isolates AI modules to prevent fault propagation.

2.9 Cross‑Platform Abstraction

A hardware abstraction layer (HAL) and middleware (DDS, ROS2) allow the same software to run on ARM, x86, RISC‑V, or cloud infrastructure, facilitating rapid prototyping and technology insertion.

